      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow account is usually held by a third-party escrow company, often a separate entity from the lender or real estate agents. These companies specialize in managing escrow accounts and are typically licensed and regulated. They act as a neutral, impartial third party, holding the funds until the transaction is complete. Think of them as a trusted, reliable middleman, rather than a bank or individual holding the money. They're responsible for disbursing the funds when the conditions are met, ensuring a smooth and secure transaction.",
